`His name is Bruin, sir,' said Biddy,
following
him.
`Bruin, Bruin! Here, Bruin!' repeated
Mr Tucker, soothingly; `come here, Bruin!
Poor fellar, Bruin!'
But Bruin wasn't to be coaxed, but stood in
